external_knowledge:
- Heavily used API endpoints refer to those that have been accessed more than 10 times; 
- Slowest average response time implies the API endpoint with the highest average response time value in milliseconds; 
- Active users are those whose accounts are currently active (`is_active = 1`);
- Frequent users are identified based on the number of times they access API endpoints.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT api_name) AS active_endpoints_count
FROM api_endpoints
WHERE is_active = 1;
